g.text: Directory Traversal Attack Vectors & Defense Pipeline
Attack Type | Input Payload | Naive strncmp Check | realpath() + Prefix Check
1. Classic Traversal | ../../../etc/passwd | [VULNERABLE] Prefix matches /var/www | [BLOCKED] Resolves to /etc/passwd
2. URL Encoded | %2e%2e%2fetc/passwd | [VULNERABLE] Prefix matches /var/www | [BLOCKED] Decodes -> Resolves to /etc/passwd
3. Double Encoded | %252e%252e%252fetc/passwd | [VULNERABLE] No '..' visible in string | [BLOCKED] Requires recursive decode or fails realpath
4. Symlink | /www/uploads/link | [VULNERABLE] Safe-looking path | [BLOCKED] realpath follows link to /etc/passwd
5. Null Byte Injection | /safe%00/../etc/passwd | [VULNERABLE] Ends in .html extension | [BLOCKED] url_decode rejects %00
